milestones.description: Ian Chappell has become the top scorer for AUS in ODIs with 230 runs, going past Stackpole's 163
Bevan Congdon has become the top scorer for NZ in ODIs with 87 runs, going past Vic Pollard's 55
Bevan Congdon's 82 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for NZ), surpassing Vic Pollard's 55
Ian Chappell's 83 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for AUS), surpassing Stackpole's 61
Ian Chappell has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (2) in ODIs for AUS, going past Ian Chappell's 1
Ian Chappell has scored 3 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, breaking Stackpole's record
Ian Chappell has broken the record for most sixes (3) in ODIs for AUS, going past Paul Sheahan's 1
Doug Walters has broken the record for most catches in an innings (3) in ODIs for AUS, going past Greg Chappell's 1
Doug Walters has broken the record for most catches (4) in ODIs for AUS, going past Mallett's 2
Ian Chappell has broken the record for most sixes (3) in ODIs, going past Hadlee's 2
Ian Chappell has scored 3 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for AUS breaking Stackpole's record
Bevan Congdon has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (40) in an innings in ODIs for NZ, going past Vic Pollard's 38
Ian Chappell has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (60) in an innings in ODIs for AUS, going past Ian Chappell's 26
Greg Chappell has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (5) for AUS, going past Ian Chappell
Mark Burgess has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (4) for NZ, going past Collinge
Doug Walters has broken the record for most catches (4) in ODIs, going past Tony Greig's 3
Dayle Hadlee and Lance Cairns's 37-run partnership is the highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 22 between Dennis Lillee and Jeff Hammond
Ian Chappell and Stackpole's 136-run partnership is AUS's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 103 between Greg Chappell and Paul Sheahan
Ian Chappell and Stackpole's 136-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 68 between Ian Chappell and Stackpole
Bevan Congdon and Glenn Turner's 12-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 8 between Bevan Congdon and Peter Coman
Bevan Congdon and Hastings's 49-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 5 between Hastings and Glenn Turner
Bevan Congdon and Mark Burgess's 33-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 4th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 17 between Mark Burgess and Hastings
Dayle Hadlee and Lance Cairns's 37-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 9th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 16 between Howarth and Hadlee
